version_description: Its a new tab for an unreleased song. So this is based solely off of one of Brandis live performances. Im open to any suggestions or corrections. Also, all of the chords are named relative to the capo on 1st fret.
The whole song is picked but strumming sounds good too.

Follows both the official songbook and live versions. In the songbook there is no capo so chords are different. Simply transpose one step up to the songbook version with no capo. This is the simpler version they play in live shows with capo on 1st fret.
The Joker is Brandi Carlile's first single from her upcoming album "By the way, I forgive you". I confirmed the chords by watching the NPR live recording from Studio A.

Just to clarify, the Dsus9 chord used throughout the song is simply an open C slid up two frets. For strumming, Brandi finger picks the whole tune, but if you give it kind of a constant, pulsing 8th note strum on the chords it creates a simpler yet similar effect.

version_description: The astericked D signifies sliding the open C shape up 2 frets for a D. Also, in the verses, believe she adds the bass G onto some of the C chords. And there are lots of hammer ons, especially with the Cs.
